FBIS3-58303 "drweu007_j_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-007 Document Type:Daily Report 11 Jan 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY Bosnia Inaction Called `Most Shameful Cowardice' AU1101130194 Paris AFP in English 1225 GMT 11 Jan 94 AU1101130194 Paris AFP Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Vatican, Jan 11 (AFP) -- The Vatican said Tuesday [11 January] the international community had committed "the crime of failing to help" end the war in the former Yugoslavia. Europe was "dying" and a collective lack of action was "the most shameful cowardice," said the Vatican's Council for Justice and Peace, in an appeal made to mark a World Day of prayers for peace in the Balkans scheduled for January 23.
